{
  "stem": "20021.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't have the option of going to America, because, you know, America wouldn't let you in at that time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The option to going to Israel was very questionable, because the British wouldn't let you in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So as best I could guess, I was being prepared that I'll probably have to go to France maybe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "France had a more liberal policy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It would let in people to study and things like that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that colored my looking to the future as far as I was growing up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But nowhere was there a serious discussion really, which should have been, in the face of what was coming.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In other words, people refuse to face up to that reality that Hitler was presenting.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They refused.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that is a story which went on throughout the war that repeats itself, that even later on, days before they were so-called resettled-- Hitler called this resettlement.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They never told them that they are taking them to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They just told them they are resettled.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And people even days before they were resettled believed that they are really being resettled to a labor camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This is a-- this part is very important to convey and to educate people about, that Hitler managed to conceal and hide.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He made a strong effort from day one, you know, to cheat and fool people, prevent them from knowing what's ahead.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for reasons, you know, which might not be so easy to explain, but I think I could explain, is the Jews were willing to accept that lie.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were willing to fool themselves.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
